-- Colombian Stock Movers: Ecopetrol, Interconexion Electrica Gain
-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 2012-01-17T14:58:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-17/colombian-stock-movers-ecopetrol-interconexion-electrica-gain.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:24 a.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  gained 0.7 percent to 13,177.60, while the
Colcap Index gained 0.5 percent to 1,585.61.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest oil producer,
gained 1 percent to 4,460 pesos. The company said yesterday
there were no “significant” production cuts because of a labor
protest.  Interconexion Electrica SA (ISA)  , Latin America’s
biggest power-line operator, rose 0.5 percent to 11,000 pesos.
The company plans to bid for energy-transmission projects in
Chile this year, Portafolio newspaper said, citing an interview
with Chief Executive Officer Luis Fernando Alarcon yesterday.  ISA, as the Medellin-based company is known, also plans to
bid for projects in Peru and Brazil, Alarcon told the Bogota-
based daily.  To contact the reporter on this story:
